President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Christopher Fonzone as General Counsel of the Office of the Director of National Intelligence, Janie Hipp as General Counsel of the Department of Agriculture, Leslie Kiernan as General Counsel of the Department of Commerce, and Todd Kim as Assistant Attorney General, Environment and Natural Resources Division, Department of Justice.

Christopher Fonzone is currently a partner in Sidley Austin's Washington D.C. office. He has served in various legal roles, including Deputy Assistant and Deputy Counsel to President Obama and Legal Adviser to the National Security Council. He has also worked at the Department of Defense and the Department of Justice.

Janie Simms Hipp has a background in agriculture law and food policy. She has worked with farmers, ranchers, and food businesses and has authored publications on agriculture and nutrition law. She has an LLM in Agriculture Law from the University of Arkansas.

Leslie B. Kiernan has experience in litigation, regulatory compliance, policy development, and enforcement matters. She served in the White House as Deputy Counsel to the President during the Obama-Biden Administration and has worked with the White House Council on Women and Girls. She currently serves as Special Counsel in the Office of the White House Counsel.

Todd Kim is currently the Deputy General Counsel for Litigation, Regulation, and Enforcement at the U.S. Department of Energy. He has previously worked as an appellate attorney with the Environment and Natural Resources Division of the U.S. Department of Justice and as the Solicitor General of the District of Columbia. He has also been a partner at Reed Smith LLP.

These nominations reflect President Biden's choices for key legal positions in various government agencies.